If you want to contribute, please let this be the skeleton of your mind:

--8<----------------
#undef USING_CXX
#undef USING_FANCY_LIBS
#include <plain_c.h>
#include <linux_kernel_coding_style.h>
#include <proper_commentary.h>
#include <skill.h> /* FIXME: But not more than ours! ;-) */
#undef WINDOWS
#undef MAC_OSX
#undef FOOBSD /* Write us if you intend to port */
#include <linux.h>
--8<----------------

and for source files, take the templates from the .vim/ directory under the
source tree. [ Beware that the repository has its own .vimrc file if you use
vim! We're also interested in scripts for other (decent!) editors. ]

Open your mailbox to us for discussion.

Don't be eccentric, I'm already.

Use Git, NOT GitHub.

Thanks.
